com.kirankunigiri.Sprint.Interpolators

Class ElasticInterpolator

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.animation.Interpolator
      • com.kirankunigiri.Sprint.Interpolators.EasingInterpolator
        • com.kirankunigiri.Sprint.Interpolators.ElasticInterpolator

  • public class ElasticInterpolator
extends EasingInterpolator
    This interpolator simulates an elastic behavior.

    The following curve illustrates the interpolation.

    The math in this class is taken from http://www.robertpenner.com/easing/.

      • baseCurve

        protected double baseCurve(double v)
        Description copied from class: EasingInterpolator
        Defines the base curve for the interpolator. The base curve is then transformed into an easing-in, easing-out easing-both curve.
        Specified by:
        baseCurve in class EasingInterpolator
        Parameters:
        v - The normalized value/time/progress of the interpolation (between 0 and 1).
        Returns:
        The resulting value of the function, should return a value between 0 and 1.
